Description: Market Network for Social Productivity
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: What is MyPeople? We're a peer-to-peer marketplace for buying, selling, and exchanging unique services and experiences. Tell me more! Services can be anything from housekeeping or logo design to a video chat with a chef helping you perfect your favorite recipe. The goal is to connect people who need help with something to someone who is available to help them. What's the story behind it? MyPeople was an idea that came to our Founder & CEO, Melissa Strawn, while she was a struggling single mom in the Bay Area with two kids to support. A short-term disability left her unable to work and she dreamt up a creative way to get her needs met while still being a valuable contributor to the economy. Melissa and her husband now have five sons and need a community of help more than ever before! They utilize the services of many of the helpers on the site and still provide services of their own. Why is this so important to you? Glad you asked! Not everyone fits into the typical workplace model. Some people have disabilities, familial responsibilities, or lack access to skills or transportation to get to the jobs that will pay them what they need. And some people just want to call their own shots! We are building a trusted community of people who offer their unique skills, talents, and services so that we can see a world where all people can earn a living doing only what they love. This comes with the bonus of knowing that you are helping lighten the load of someone else.

Description: CFS Foundry is a professional investment casting company, we specialise in investment casting of different alloys.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: CFS Foundry is a reputable and professional investment casting company renowned for its expertise in producing high-quality castings from a variety of materials, including stainless steel, carbon steel, alloy steel, and nickel-based alloys. Specializing in the lost wax casting process, CFS Foundry is committed to delivering precision-engineered components with exceptional accuracy, intricate details, and superior surface finishes. With a track record of excellence in the industry, we cater to diverse sectors such as aerospace, automotive, energy, and many more. Utilizing the lost wax casting process, CFS Foundry ensures the production of intricate and complex components with minimal material waste. This method begins with the creation of a detailed wax or plastic pattern, which is then coated in ceramic slurry to form a mold. After the mold is heated, the wax or plastic melts away, leaving behind a cavity that is filled with molten metal. The result is a precise and dimensionally accurate casting that meets stringent industry standards. CFS Foundry's dedication to quality extends beyond the casting process itself. Our experienced team of engineers and metallurgists closely monitors every step of production, from design and pattern-making to final inspection. This commitment to quality control ensures that customers receive castings that meet their exact specifications, whether for prototypes, small batches, or high-volume production runs. With a strong emphasis on customer satisfaction, CFS Foundry is a trusted partner for companies seeking reliable investment casting solutions for their critical applications.

Description: MailerMailer is a DIY email marketing and list management service provider.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: MailerMailer is an award-winning do-it-yourself email marketing and list management provider. Equipped with the latest email marketing technology, such as zip code radius targeting, image hosting, and custom email templates, MailerMailer allows easy creation of professional email newsletters and campaigns. HISTORY Brothers Raj and Vivek Khera founded MailerMailer in early 2001, shortly after selling their previous venture, GovCon, to a publicly traded company in 1999. GovCon, which they founded in 1995, had quickly become the largest government contracting portal in the world. As they grew GovCon, the Khera brothers faced several challenges around sending weekly newsletters to their client base. The in-house tools they had did not offer tracking capabilities or list management to handle bounces and unsubscribe requests automatically. The only available email marketing tools for small businesses at the time were expensive and cumbersome to use. So, when the duo sold GovCon and set their sights on a new venture, they saw an opportunity to help other companies manage their email newsletters at an affordable price. Their goal in creating MailerMailer was to develop an intuitive email marketing tool for non-technical people. They kept in mind that most of the “high end” features in other services are only be used by a small percentage of clients. This put the focus on the most commonly used features that a small business would want in an email marketing tool and on the interface to make the user experience very friendly. As MailerMailer began acquiring larger customers, they were part of the early dialogues with ISPs to build whitelisting processes that are in place today.
Industry Groups: Information Technology, Internet Services, Messaging and Telecommunications, Sales and Marketing, Software

Description: Instalocate is an AI powered personal travel assistant to make your journey comfortable. It is like Google Now++ for Travel.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Instalocate is an AI powered personal travel assistant to make your journey comfortable. It is like Google Now++ for Travel. Instalocate's Internet of Moving Things platform tracks public transport in real time and by using Artificial Intelligence, it provides the most relevant information just at the right time. Their mission is to bring peace of mind to people’s life by helping them track anything that is traceable - be your plane, cab, train, bus, food delivery, pet, and even your spouse! They take a first step towards their mission by launching the travel assistant for air travel. The travel assistant is available on Facebook Messenger at m.me/instalocate. No need to install a new app! Just share your flight details and it will handle the rest. It predicts when you might need something and sends the contextual information automatically. It informs you if your flight is getting delayed. If you are wondering if the airport has free Wi-Fi, just ask your assistant. If your family is worried about you, the assistant can pinpoint your exact location in the air. They don’t have to anxiously wait outside the airport checking their phones again and again! After reaching your destination, your cab will be waiting for you. Stanford University and Indian Institute of Management (IIM) alumni founded Instalocate in June 2016. They are passionately working at the intersection of Artificial Intelligence and Internet of Moving Things. The team consists of enthusiastic engineers with strong background in AI, Web Search, Machine Learning, Big Data and Mobile. Conversational AI revolution has just started and the team is taking up the challenge head-on!

Description: Bovigen LLC, a genomics company, engages in the development, validation, and commercialization of genetic tools that enable producers to
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Bovigen LLC, a genomics company, engages in the development, validation, and commercialization of genetic tools that enable producers to impact the economics of the beef industry. It offers DNA diagnostic test products, such as Feed Efficiency, a test to identify difference in feed cost in animals; Tenderness, a multi-marker single trait test for identifying animals that produce tender cuts of beef; and Quality Grade, a DNA genetic marker panel test that identifies the presence of genes associated with quality grade and marbling. The company also provides SureTRAK, an innovative genetic testing system for traceability of animals and meat; SireTRACE, which is used to identify animals through DNA fingerprinting; BLACK test, a coat color test that is primarily used to identify black coat genes in black animals; and Elite Tender that enables restaurants, retailers, and food service distributors to check for tender beef in buying and serving. It distributes its products through various companies and individuals in the United States, as well as in Canada, Central America, and South America. The company was founded in 2003 and is based in Harahan, Louisiana. As of March 27, 2008, Bovigen LLC operates as a subsidiary of Pfizer Animal Health.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering
